======================

Currently serverscope-benchmark supports following distro:

* Debian 9, 10
* CentOS 7, 8
* Ubuntu 16.04, 18.04, 20.04, 20.10, 21.04

Use https://github.com/serverscope/serverscope-benchmark/raw/master/install-serverscope.sh
to install serverscope-benchmark package in your system.

Some notes about install-serverscope.sh:

----------------------
CentOS notes:

* CentOS 7 enables uses EPEL repo in order to satisfy runtime dependencies (python36 from EPEL)

----------------------
Ubuntu notes:

* Ubuntu 16.04 installs additional python3-distro in order to satisfy distro missing dep

======================

You can also build the packages manually.
Clone the project from

  https://github.com/serverscope/serverscope-benchmark.git

and use:

  make rpm (make deb)

======================
All other distributions may manually install following packages in your system:

  fio, gcc, make, which, python3, perl, python3-distro, python3-requests, python3-setuptools

Clone the project from

  https://github.com/serverscope/serverscope-benchmark.git

and use:

  python3 setup.py install
